<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="id80b5ec0d-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="miscellaneous" id="id80b5ec0e-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Termination of War and Emergencies</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Joint Res. <ref href="/us/act/1947-07-25/ch327/s3">July 25, 1947, ch. 327, § 3</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/61/451">61 Stat. 451</ref>, provided that in the interpretation of former <ref href="/us/usc/t40/s276a–5">40 U.S.C. 276a–5</ref>, the date <date date="1947-07-25">July 25, 1947</date>, was to be deemed to be the date of termination of any state of war theretofore declared by Congress and of the national emergencies proclaimed by the President on <date date="1939-09-08">September 8, 1939</date>, and <date date="1941-05-27">May 27, 1941</date>.</p>
</note>
